fish and chip brigade
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Name given to group of young Labour MPs who ate together regularly from the fish and chip shop opposite Parliament and were responsible for the first abortive and late successful coups to replace Rowling and subsequently became Ministers in the Lange Rogernomics Cabinet.
